<doc>
  <member name="ID3D11ShaderResourceView1.GetDesc1">
    <summary>
      <para>Gets the shader-resource view's description.</para>
    </summary>
    <param name="pDesc1">
      <para>Type: <b><see cref="D3D11_SHADER_RESOURCE_VIEW_DESC1" />*</b></para>
      <para>A pointer to a <see cref="D3D11_SHADER_RESOURCE_VIEW_DESC1" /> structure that receives the description of the shader-resource view.</para>
    </param>
    <seealso cref="ID3D11ShaderResourceView1" />
  </member>
  <member name="ID3D11ShaderResourceView1">
    <summary>
      <para>A shader-resource-view interface represents the subresources a shader can access during rendering. Examples of shader resources include a constant buffer, a texture buffer, and a texture.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>To create a shader-resource view, call <see cref="ID3D11Device3.CreateShaderResourceView1" />.</para>
      <para>A shader-resource view is required when binding a resource to a shader stage; the binding occurs by calling <see cref="ID3D11DeviceContext.GSSetShaderResources" />, <see cref="ID3D11DeviceContext.VSSetShaderResources" /> or <see cref="ID3D11DeviceContext.PSSetShaderResources" />.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso cref="ID3D11ShaderResourceView" />
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d11/d3d11-graphics-reference-resource-interfaces">Resource Interfaces</seealso>
  </member>
</doc>